  "text": "This security audit identifies HTTP handlers registered without authentication middleware in the Grafana Loki and Mimir logging and metrics systems.\n\n**Mimir (grafana/mimir:pkg/api/api.go)**: The Mimir API module registers numerous HTTP endpoints through methods like RegisterAPI, RegisterDistributor, RegisterIngester, RegisterRuler, RegisterStoreGateway, RegisterCompactor, RegisterQueryScheduler, and RegisterAlertmanager. These methods call RegisterRoute() with the auth parameter set to false for operational and diagnostic endpoints including:\n\n- Configuration and status endpoints: /config, /api/v1/status/config, /api/v1/status/flags, /api/v1/status/buildinfo, /runtime_config, / (index)\n- Static assets and debugging: /static/, /debug/fgprof\n- Component operational endpoints: /distributor/ring, /distributor/all_user_stats, /distributor/ha_tracker, /ingester/flush, /ingester/prepare-shutdown, /ingester/prepare-partition-downscale, /ingester/tenants, /ingester/tsdb/{tenant}, /ruler/ring, /ruler/tenants, /store-gateway/ring, /store-gateway/tenants, /compactor/ring, /compactor/tenants, /querier/ring, /query-scheduler/ring\n- Alertmanager endpoints: /multitenant_alertmanager/status, /multitenant_alertmanager/configs, /multitenant_alertmanager/ring\n- Cost attribution metrics: /cost-attribution\n\nThe newRoute() function (line 164-186) conditionally applies authentication middleware only when the auth parameter is true. The RegisterRoute() and RegisterDeprecatedRoute() methods pass auth=false for these endpoints, meaning they bypass middleware.AuthenticateUser.\n\n**Loki (grafana/loki:pkg/loki/modules.go)**: The Loki modules file registers multiple ring status pages and operational endpoints without explicit authentication middleware, including endpoints in initRing(), initDistributor(), initIngester(), and other module initialization functions. These expose internal component ring status and cluster membership information.\n\n**Loki (grafana/loki:pkg/ingester/ingester.go)**: The ingester package defines HTTP handler methods including FlushHandler, ShutdownHandler, PrepareShutdownHandler, and PreparePartitionDownscaleHandler that perform administrative operations (triggering flushes, initiating shutdown sequences) without visible authentication enforcement at the handler level.\n\n**Loki (grafana/loki:pkg/querier/http.go)**: The querier package implements multiple HTTP query handlers (RangeQueryHandler, InstantQueryHandler, LabelHandler, SeriesHandler, VolumeHandler, DetectedFieldsHandler, PatternsHandler, DetectedLabelsHandler) that process user queries. These handlers are registered without explicit authentication middleware application.\n\nWhile Mimir explicitly shows auth=false parameters indicating deliberate choice to skip authentication for operational endpoints, Loki's handlers are registered without visible authentication middleware wrapping. Both systems rely on authentication enforcement at the reverse proxy or outer middleware layer rather than at individual handler registration points. This design assumes network-level security controls are in place to protect these endpoints."
}

